The following companies had unusual
price changes in Argentine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of the close in  Buenos
Aires .  The  Merval (MERVAL)  Index fell 0.3 percent to 2,684.18.  Banco Patagonia SA (BPAT)   rose 1.5 percent to 3.44
pesos. The Argentine lender will buy back as much as 3.45
million pesos ($789,184) of its own shares within the next 180
days to bolster their value after the stock fell below book
value, it said in a statement posted yesterday on the website of
the Buenos Aires exchange.  Tenaris SA (TEN)   fell 0.6 percent to 101.9 pesos. The
worldâ€™s largest producer of seamless steel tubes used in the oil
